[LOG]
Date: 2026‑03‑06
Category: ultramode_patcher_rules_full
Version: 6.4

CORE SYSTEM RULES:
- 100% Python (Pygame UI)
- No Bash logic anywhere
- Controller + keyboard unified
- Folder‑per‑module architecture
- Every module is a Python package
- All modules stored in:
    /userdata/system/ultramode/patcher/modules/<module_name>/
- Main program stored in:
    /userdata/system/ultramode/patcher/patcher.py
- Buffer stored in:
    /userdata/system/ultramode/patcher/buffer.txt
- Backups stored in:
    /userdata/system/ultramode/backups/
- Logs stored in:
    /userdata/system/ultramode/logs/

PERMANENT RULES:
- Permanent “Hi Mom.” line must exist in main patcher
- Version starts at v6 and increments on ANY change
- Address bar always visible:
    UltraMode > Patcher > <Module>
- 80‑column aware layout
- LEFT/RIGHT reserved for future submenus
- Bottom help bar always visible
- Idle silly‑message rotation allowed
- Warn before ANY system modification
- No deleting or modifying existing log lines — append only
- Every file in every module must end with:
    ###EOL###

MODULE FILES (REQUIRED IN EVERY MODULE):
- __init__.py
- meta.py        (title, version, folder path, EOL marker)
- ui.py          (drawing, layout, colors)
- logic.py       (actions, patching, backup, restore)
- input.py       (controller + keyboard mapping)
- state.py       (shared state, constants)
- ###EOL### at end of every file

MAIN MENU ITEMS:
1. Apply Patch From Buffer
2. Apply Patch To Existing File
3. Backup System
4. Restore Backup
5. Developer Tools
6. Exit

BUFFER SYSTEM RULES:
- Buffer is plain text file:
    /userdata/system/ultramode/patcher/buffer.txt
- User pastes patch code into buffer
- “Apply Patch From Buffer” reads buffer.txt
- Buffer must support ULTRAMODE PATCH SPEC:
    FULL
    DIFF
    BLOCK
    APPEND
- Buffer must be validated before execution
- If buffer empty → error
- If buffer invalid → syntax error
- If buffer valid → run patch engine

PATCH ENGINE RULES:
- Validate syntax before running
- Dry‑run mode required
- Automatic backup before patching
- Rollback on failure
- Patch history stored in:
    /userdata/system/ultramode/logs/patch_history.log
- No partial writes allowed
- Must show success/failure message

BACKUP SYSTEM RULES:
- Full system backup
- Restore from latest backup
- Verify backup integrity
- Backups stored in:
    /userdata/system/ultramode/backups/
- Backup names must include timestamp
- Restore must warn user before proceeding

DEVELOPER TOOLS:
- View logs
- Validate patch spec
- Inspect module metadata
- Show controller input diagnostics
- Show Python environment info
- Show module folder paths

UI RULES:
- Centered menu
- Highlighted selected item
- Description line under menu
- Bottom help bar always visible
- TV‑visible colors
- No clutter
- 80‑column awareness

